Retail Sales Analysis Project

Overview
This project analyzes retail sales data for the year 2023 using Excel, SQL, and Power BI. 
The goal was to clean raw data, perform exploratory data analysis (EDA), and build an interactive dashboard.

Tools Used
Excel (Data Cleaning & Pivot Tables)
MySQL (EDA & Advanced Queries)
Power BI (Dashboard Visualization)

Data Cleaning
Handled missing values (UNKNOWN, ERROR, blanks)
Recalculated incorrect values (Total Spent, Quantity)
Standardized categories (Payment Method, Location)
Managed missing dates and formatted columns

Key Insights
Top Product: Salad generated the highest revenue
Peak Month: June had the highest sales (~7350)
Payment Issue: Large revenue categorized as "Unknown"
Location Issue: Missing location data impacted the analysis


Dashboard Features
KPI Cards (Total Revenue, Transactions, AOV)
Sales by Item (Bar Chart)
Monthly Trend (Line Chart)
Payment Method Distribution (Pie Chart)
Location Analysis (Column Chart)
Interactive Filters (Month, Item, Payment Method)

SQL Analysis
Performed advanced queries, including:
Revenue aggregation
Top products
Monthly trends
Window functions (LAG) for growth analysis


Files Included
Dataset (CSV)
SQL queries
Dashboard screenshot

Conclusion
This project demonstrates an end-to-end data analysis workflow from raw data to business insights using multiple tools.
